# Creating GitLab Merge Requests

This repo is hosted on **gitlab.rechargeapps.net** (not github.com).
`glab` CLI is NOT configured for this host, so use the REST API directly.

## Project

- **Web**: https://gitlab.rechargeapps.net/engineering/subscriptions/mealkit-demo-portal
- **Merge requests**: https://gitlab.rechargeapps.net/engineering/subscriptions/mealkit-demo-portal/-/merge_requests
- **Path**: `engineering/subscriptions/mealkit-demo-portal`
- **Clone**: `https://gitlab.rechargeapps.net/engineering/subscriptions/mealkit-demo-portal.git`

## Prerequisites

- The GitLab token is in the `GITLAB_TOKEN` env var (already set in shell sessions).
- The project numeric ID is **1118**.
- The project path is `engineering/subscriptions/mealkit-demo-portal`.

## Steps

### 1. Create and push the branch

```bash
cd /Users/tarek/Documents/demo-portal/future-charge-manipulation-demo-portal
git checkout -b feature/your-branch-name
git add <files>
git commit -m "Your commit message"
git push -u origin feature/your-branch-name
```

### 2. Create the MR via API

```bash
curl --silent --request POST \
  --header "PRIVATE-TOKEN: $GITLAB_TOKEN" \
  --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --data '{
    "source_branch": "feature/your-branch-name",
    "target_branch": "master",
    "title": "Your MR title",
    "description": "Your MR description (supports markdown)",
    "remove_source_branch": true
  }' \
  "https://gitlab.rechargeapps.net/api/v4/projects/1118/merge_requests" \
  | python3 -c "import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('web_url', d))"
```

The default target branch is `master`. Change if needed.

### Common API operations

```bash
# List open MRs
curl --silent --header "PRIVATE-TOKEN: $GITLAB_TOKEN" \
  "https://gitlab.rechargeapps.net/api/v4/projects/1118/merge_requests?state=opened"

# Get a specific MR
curl --silent --header "PRIVATE-TOKEN: $GITLAB_TOKEN" \
  "https://gitlab.rechargeapps.net/api/v4/projects/1118/merge_requests/MR_IID"

# Add a comment to an MR
curl --silent --request POST \
  --header "PRIVATE-TOKEN: $GITLAB_TOKEN" \
  --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --data '{"body": "Your comment"}' \
  "https://gitlab.rechargeapps.net/api/v4/projects/1118/merge_requests/MR_IID/notes"
```
